                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14687.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The matter pertaining to situation on border, Department’s March 24, was
                    presented to Mr. Zubaran as General Carranza continues sick in bed. I was
                    assured that immediate orders would be given to avoid the possibility
                    feared.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
